properties.Name: InsuranceClauseType
properties.Description:
A type of clause that is applied either an Insurance Product or a specific insurance product.

A clause is a section in an insurance product that explains, defines or clarifies the conditions of coverage.

Ex:
Abandonment Clause.
A clause in fire insurance policies and other property forms that prohibits the insured from abandoning partially damaged property to the insurer in order to claim a total loss.

Automatic Reinstatement Clause.
A stipulation in a Property insurance product which states that after a partial loss covered by the policy has been paid, the original limit of the policy will be automatically reinstated.
